    "body": "### Problem\n\nhi friends!\n\nthe file contains just a txt file with no extension, a large 500 MB file with lines like name, phone, etc and ^M as line breaks, for some reason, breaks when opening it says 'debug using malloc' \n\nnvim(36403,0x1f9700f80) malloc: Incorrect checksum for freed object 0x168b24200: probably modified after being freed.\n\nCorrupt value: 0x64654d3a656c616d\n\nnvim(36403,0x1f9700f80) malloc: *** set a breakpoint in malloc_error_break to debug  \n\n```\n➜  col 2 git:(main) ✗ vi --version         \nNVIM v0.10.3\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1713484068\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n➜  col 2 git:(main) ✗ vi -V1 -v        \nNVIM v0.10.3\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1713484068\n\n   system vimrc file: \"$VIM/sysinit.vim\"\n  fall-back for $VIM: \"/usr/local/share/nvim\"\n\nRun :checkhealth for more info\n➜  col 2 git:(main) ✗ \n```\n\nI don't have weird stuff installed.\nthe previous GVIM seems to open the file just fine, this is the first time in 20 years of using vim I see a crash when opening big files, I am not sure what to do here.\n\nis vim supposed to be able to open 500MB files with 10-20m lines or so?\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nopen a 500 mb file, on osx\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nit should not crash with strange errors\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 9.1 seems to open just fine\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDarwin m1machine.local 23.6.0 Darwin Kernel Version 23.6.0: Thu Dec 19 20:47:33 PST 2024; root:xnu-10063.141.1.703.2~1/RELEASE_ARM64_T8103 arm64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nI don't remember I think i downloaded it and put it in a folder it lives on $HOME/nvim/nvim-macos-arm64/bin/nvim but I don't think I compiled it, it doesn't look like it is homebrew either",
